- used to create, store and manage encrytpion keys

- centrally manage crypographic keys within aws

- inetgrates with many aws services

- Logs key usage within aws cloudtrail logs for compliance and audits

CMK

- Customer master key: holds key material to encrypt data.

- cmks can only encrypt up to 4kb of data

- generate, encrypt and decrypt the data key

- Data key: used to encrypt and decrypt your data

- alias: apps can refer to the alias when using the cmk

- Key state
  - enabled
  - disabled
  - pending
  - deletion
  - Unavailable

- CMK always live in KMS, can never be exported

KMS CLI COMMANDS

- aws kms encrypt/decrypt
- aws kms re-encrypt
- aws kms enable-key-rotation
